column1: i have the 13600kf and is a very cool cpu i love it

awesome job intel i have to say the 13600k impresses me a heck of a lot more than the 13900k the 13900k may be able to do much better overall but the value proposition on the 13600k is absurdly good was not expecting this level of a generational improvement aside from power and thermals and apparently neither was amd
holy shit the 5800x3d is on par with the 13600k ddr5 6400 in the 12 game average thats incredibly impressive and means that if youre already on am4 getting a 5800x3d is the way to go
thanks for doing this review another review i had watched yesterday arrived at the same conclusion about 13600k competition is great
intel definitely made a good choice to pack 8 e cores with the 13600k its basically a 14 core 20 thread cpu and thats why it beats the 7600x so easily in the productivity aspect
thank you for testing the 13600k on ddr5 and ddr4

hey guys
thank you for the amazing work
as you always advice i have watched reviews from multiple channels for the comparison between 7600x and 13600k
but these reviews use a 40903090ti to highlight the performance difference

intels ecores are a blessing for rendering and productivity where they can be used to great extent for gaming theyre not as valuable but can be used for other background things especially because there are only 6 performance cores for the i513600k which can then be focused for gaming

13600k is 2 cents more cost effective per frame

steve as you can see this chip clearly stomps all over everything and is the only choice for budget conscious gamers that will be all see you next time

so basically horizon brought the 7600x to the 13600k level i guess it could be because horizon was originally optimized for amd architecture from the get go for ps4 either way both cpus are pretty good
